'''G<U+00FC>rz<U+0259>''' is a variation of [[Azerbaijan]]i [[dumpling]]s consisting of a filling wrapped in 1mm thin [[dough]] circle cuts of 5 cm diameter. It originates in Azerbaijan and is a part of [[Azerbaijani cuisine|Azerbaijan national cuisine]]. The filling is made from [[mince]]d fatty [[Lamb and mutton|lamb]] and onion, pre-fried before filling. G<U+00FC>rz<U+0259> are formed as small cylinders with an open top, boiled for several minutes, strained, seasoned with [[cinnamon]] and served with yogurt or sour cream mixed with crushed garlic. In some regions of Azerbaijan G<U+00FC>rz<U+0259> dumplings are boiled in lamb stock and served as a soup, seasoned with chopped fresh parsley and served with vinegar mix and crushed garlic <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metbex.net/xemir/gurz%c9%99.html|title=G<U+00FC>rz<U+0259>|accessdate=13 May 2011 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://azerbaijan.tourism.az/index.php?/az/topmenu_content/968= |title=Azerbaijan Tourism - G<U+00FC>rz<U+0259> |accessdate= 13 May 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.metbex.net/sorbalar/s%C9%99kisayagi-gurz%C9%99.html |title=Milli m<U+0259>tb<U+0259>x. <U+015E><U+0259>kisaya<U+011F><U+0131> g<U+00FC>rz<U+0259> | accessdate=13 May 2011}}</ref>
The name  "G<U+00FC>rz<U+0259>" is associated with [[Azerbaijan language|Azerbaijani]] name for "Caucasian meadow viper" (''[[Vipera lotievi]]'') and given due to the wrapper sealing technique, which resembles cornrow pattern on the skin of Caucasian meadow viper.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://eda.ru/recipe/5210/ |title= Eda. <U+0413><U+044E><U+0440><U+0437><U+0430> |accessdate= 16 May 2011}}</ref> 

